      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__gpio__api_1gaa5b62394f65ecbb6566d91412616509c" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void XGpio_InterruptEnable</definition>
        <argsstring>(XGpio *InstancePtr, u32 Mask)</argsstring>
        <name>XGpio_InterruptEnable</name>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="struct_x_gpio" kindref="compound">XGpio</ref> *</type>
          <declname>InstancePtr</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>u32</type>
          <declname>Mask</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Enable interrupts. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The global interrupt must also be enabled by calling <ref refid="group__gpio__api_1ga116bf1509220aa688f76f80501eb0d9e" kindref="member">XGpio_InterruptGlobalEnable()</ref> for interrupts to occur. This function will assert if the hardware device has not been built with interrupt capabilities.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>GPIO instance to operate on. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Mask</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Mask to enable. Bit positions of 1 are enabled. This mask is formed by OR&apos;ing bits from XGPIO_IR* bits which are contained in <ref refid="xgpio__l_8h" kindref="compound">xgpio_l.h</ref>.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>None. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
